        <p>
            Phishing attacks can have devastating consequences for businesses of all sizes. By tricking employees into divulging sensitive information, such as login credentials or financial data, cybercriminals can gain unauthorised access to corporate networks. This can lead to data breaches, financial losses, and damage to the company’s reputation. In severe cases, it can even result in legal liabilities and loss of customer trust. It’s crucial for organizations to educate their employees on how to recognize and avoid phishing attempts. Regular training and simulated phishing exercises can help in reducing the likelihood of successful attacks, thereby protecting the business and its stakeholders.
